{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/memoryinputstreamsignalname\/notify"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The notify signal is emitted on an object when one of its properties has"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"its value set through "},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set()"},{"type":"text","text":", et al."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that getting this signal doesn’t itself guarantee that the value of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then any call to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" results","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If they did pass [explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then this signal is emitted only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when they explicitly call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"t